<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>";s:10:"post_title";s:101:"Emma Stone Career, Upcoming Projects, Personal Life, Achievements, Net Worth: How Rich is Emma Stone?";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:95:"emma-stone-career-upcoming-projects-personal-life-achievements-net-worth-how-rich-is-emma-stone";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2018-03-19 00:08:56";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2018-03-18 18:23:56";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:28:"http://wikiceleb.com/?p=1558";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1588";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2018-03-26 23:03:20";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2018-03-26 17:18:20";s:12:"post_content";s:9096:"<p style="text-align: justify;">He has certainly got the looks that has kept women of all ages drooling over him for years and now with his much intense and sincere portrayal of the much beloved comic character Captain America he is adored by everyone- he is none other than the handsome actor and film maker <strong><em>Chris</em> Evans</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Born in Boston, Massachusetts on 13 June 1981 <strong><em>Christopher Robert</em> <em>Evans</em></strong> is the third child to a dentist father G. Robert Evans and mother Lisa who is an artistic director at the Concord Youth theatre. He was raised in Sudbury and graduated from Lincoln-Sudbury Regional High School. He later took his acting classes from Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute, New York.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1590" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wallpaper.wiki-Captain-america-chris-evans-wallpaper-full-hd-PIC-WPC006491-300x188.jpg" alt="" width="548" height="344" />
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Career</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris was filmed for the first time in a short educational video named <strong><em>Biodiversity: Wild about Life</em></strong> in 1997.¬† He commenced his career as a model for Tyler in Hasbro‚Äôs Board game <strong><em>Mystery Date</em></strong> in 1999. After getting much encouragement from his friends he started giving auditions for televisions and films as a result he starred in a TV series <strong><em>Opposite Sex</em></strong> in 2000. Then, he was seen in some episodes of other television series such as <strong><em>The Fugitive</em></strong> (2000), <strong><em>Boston Public</em></strong> (2001), <strong><em>Skin</em></strong> (2003), <strong><em>Robert Chicken</em></strong> (2008) and <strong><em>Agent Carter</em></strong> (2015).</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1591" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/The-Chris-Evans-Blog-090711-016-300x187.jpg" alt="" width="547" height="341" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Evans debuted in movies in 2000 from the film <strong><em>The Newcomers</em></strong>. He gained recognition from his 2001 movie <strong><em>Not another Teen Movie</em></strong>. Chris was praised for his acting in the movie and thus landed solo roles in movies such as in an American teen comedy heist movie <strong><em>The Perfect Score</em></strong> (2004), an action crime thriller <strong><em>Cellular</em></strong> (2004), a drama thriller <strong><em>Fierce People</em></strong> (2005) and an independent film <strong><em>London</em></strong> (2005).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Later, in 2005 he landed the role of Johnny Storm/ Human Torch in the movie <strong><em>Fantastic Four</em></strong> and reprised the same role in the 2007 sequel <strong><em>Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer</em></strong>. The performance of Chris was loved both by critics and the audiences and the movie did a good business in the box office. In the subsequent years, Evans did various movies like a science fiction thriller movie <strong><em>Sunshine</em></strong> (2007), an American comedy-drama <strong><em>The Nanny Diaries</em></strong> (2007), a crime thriller movie <strong>Street <em>Kings</em></strong> (2008), an action thriller <strong><em>Push</em></strong> (2009), an action comedy The <strong><em>Losers</em></strong> (2010), a comedy film <strong><em>Scott pilgrim vs The World</em></strong> (2010), crime thriller <strong><em>The Iceman</em></strong> (2012) along with a science fiction movie <strong><em>Snowpiecer</em></strong> (2013).</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1592" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/chris-evans-actor-in-sports-suit-hd-image-300x189.jpg" alt="" width="547" height="345" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris got his much awaited major and breakthrough role as Steve Rogers/ Captain America in <strong><em>Captain America: The First Avenger</em></strong> in 2011 and reprised the same role in first in the movie <strong><em>The Avengers</em></strong> (2012) and <strong><em>Captain America: The Winter Soldier</em></strong> in 2014. He again reprised the role in <strong>Avengers: Age of the <em>Ultron</em></strong> in 2015 and <strong>Captain America: Civil <em>War</em></strong> in 2016 alongside <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/tom-holland-career-personal-life-net-worth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tom Holland</a>, Robert Downey Jr, Scarlett Johanson and many more. Chris has also done a cameo role in <strong><em>Thor: The Dark World</em></strong> (2013) and <strong><em>Spiderman: Homecoming</em></strong> in 2017. All of these are under <strong><em>Marvels Cinematic Universe</em></strong> and all of them have done exceptionally well in the box office being one of the highest grossing movies in their respective year. Moreover, the performance of Chris was immensely praised and loved globally.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1593" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/fotonoticia_20151213111747_1280-300x181.jpg" alt="" width="542" height="327" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">In addition, Evans has executively produced and acted in an American independent romantic drama film <strong><em>Before We Go</em></strong> (2014) and featured in a drama film <strong><em>Gifted</em></strong> (2017) from where he got recognition as a drama movie actor as well.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Upcoming projects</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1594" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/4cbc049796772d98e51bf790e0b8aee4-300x184.jpg" alt="" width="543" height="333" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris Evans is a dedicated actor. He is set to reprise his beloved role of Steve Rogers/Captain America in much anticipated movies <strong><em>Avengers: Infinity war</em></strong> and its <strong><em>untitled sequel</em></strong> which is to be released in 2018 and 2019 respectively. Furthermore, Chris will also be seen in a biographic drama titled <strong><em>The Red Sea Diving Resort</em></strong> in 2018.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Personal Life</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1595" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/d375d9e8065b9ce5c68167aeca99ea17-300x208.jpg" alt="" width="546" height="378" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris owns a mansion in Hollywood hills but loves to spend time in his home town Boston. He has two sisters Carly and Shanna both of them are theatre actors and his younger brother Scott was seen in ABC series <strong><em>One Life to Live</em></strong>. He is a catholic. Chris has been linked with many actresses and models such as Kate Bosworth, Jessica Biel, Christina Rocci along with his childhood crush Sandra Bullock. Recently, he was dating actress <strong><em>Jenny Slate</em></strong> but the couple ended their one year long relationship in 2017.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Achievements</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1596" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/chris-evans-peoples-choice-08jan15-01-300x223.jpg" alt="" width="552" height="410" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Evans is an extremely proficient actor. He has won many awards mainly for his performance as <strong><em>Captain America</em></strong>. He won the <strong><em>Best Superhero Award</em></strong> from <strong><em>Scream Awards</em></strong> for his movie <strong><em>Captain America: The First Avenger</em></strong> in 2011. He also acclaimed <strong><em>The Favourite Action Movie Actor Award</em></strong> by <strong><em>People‚Äôs Choice Awards</em></strong> in 2015 for his performance in <strong><em>Captain America: The Winter Soldier</em></strong>. Additionally, he also won <strong><em>Choice Movie Scene Stealer Award</em></strong> from <strong><em>Teen Choice Awards</em></strong> for <strong><em>Avengers: Age of Ultron</em></strong> in 2015. Chris was also honored with <strong><em>Choice Movie Actor: Sci/Fi Fantasy</em></strong> and <strong><em>Favourite Butt-Kicker Award</em></strong> from <strong><em>Teen Choice Awards</em></strong> and <strong><em>Kids‚Äô Choice Award</em></strong> respectively in 2016 for his movie <strong><em>Captain America: Civil War</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Net-Worth</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Christopher Evans lives a lavish lifestyle. He bought his mansion of Hollywood Hills for $3.5 million.¬† He has a salary of $7,000,000 and the net worth of Chris Evans is reported to be $50 million.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris Evans is a wonderful actor and a gem of a person. With his incredible performance as Captain America he has proved the entire world that he is not just a handsome face by the help of his sheer hard work and we are pretty sure that he will be able to stick to the list of A-list actors in the forthcoming days as well.</p>
<a href="http://www.wikiceleb.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.wikiceleb.com</a>";s:10:"post_title";s:77:"Chris Evans Career, Upcoming Projects, Personal Life, Achievements, Net worth";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:73:"chris-evans-career-upcoming-projects-personal-life-achievements-net-worth";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2018-03-26 23:04:28";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2018-03-26 17:19:28";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:28:"http://wikiceleb.com/?p=1588";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:9;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1602";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2018-04-04 23:54:35";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2018-04-04 18:09:35";s:12:"post_content";s:12941:"<p style="text-align: justify;">An actress, a singer, a model, a peerless sex symbol and what not this actress is extremely beautiful and tremendously talented who has achieved a place as an A-list actress in the entertainment industry by her powerful performances.she is none other than the ravishing <strong><em>Scarlett Johansson</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><em>Scarlett</em></strong><strong> <em>Ingrid Johansson</em></strong> was born on 22 November, 1984 in Manhattan, New York to an architect father Karsten Olaf Johansson and a producer mother Melanie Sloan. She grew up in a family with limited means and studied in PS 41 elementary school, Manhattan. As to pursue her passion for acting she enrolled in Lee Strasberg Theatre Institute and Professional children‚Äôs School.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Career</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">At an early age, Scarlett made her first stage appearance in an Off-Broadway play <strong><em>Sophistry</em></strong> where she had only two lines. In 2010, she returned back to the theatres through a play titled <strong><em>A view from the Bridge</em></strong> and again in 2013 she starred in a play named <strong><em>Cat on a Hot Tin Roof</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1604" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Scarlett-Johansson-Wallpaper-300x175.jpg" alt="" width="585" height="341" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Johansson first appeared in an episode of the TV series <strong><em>The Client</em></strong> in 1995. Similarly, she appeared in a few episodes of some TV series like <strong><em>Anatomy of a Scene</em></strong> (2001), <strong><em>Entourage</em></strong> (2004), <strong><em>Robert Chicken</em></strong> (2005, 2006, 2008), <strong><em>HitRecord</em></strong> on TV (2014) and <strong><em>Saturday Night Live!</em></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Scarlett Johansson has a very interesting journey as far as movies are concerned. She debuted in movies by a filmed titled <strong><em>North</em></strong> in 1994. She then featured in many minor roles in films such as a suspense thriller <strong><em>Just Cause</em></strong> (1995), a rom-com <strong><em>If Lucy fell</em></strong> (1996), a comedy drama <strong><em>Manny &amp; Lo</em></strong> (1996), a family comedy <strong><em>Home Alone 3</em></strong>¬† (1997),¬† a drama <strong><em>The Horse Whisperer</em></strong> (1998), a crime film <strong><em>The Man Who wasn‚Äôt there</em></strong> (2001). Later, she got recognized by her performance in the movies <strong><em>Ghost World</em></strong> (2001) and a horror movie <strong><em>Eight Legged Freaks</em></strong> (2001).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1605" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/hd-scarlett-johansson-amazing-still-mobile-photo-free-background-300x182.jpg" alt="" width="584" height="354" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">During her late teens, Scarlett transitioned to adult roles by two movies titled <strong><em>Lost in Translation</em></strong> (2003) and <strong><em>Girl with a Pearl Earring</em></strong> (2004). Both the movies were commercial success and she was widely admired worldwide. Then, in 2004 she gave two good movies out of her five releases which were <strong><em>A Love Song for Bobby Long</em></strong> and a voice role in <strong><em>The Sponge Bob Square Pants</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In the subsequent years, Johansson has done several projects which includes a psychological thriller <strong><em>Match point</em></strong> (2005), a sci-fi action thriller <strong><em>The Island</em></strong> (2005), a rom-com thriller <strong><em>Scoop</em></strong> (2006), a crime thriller <strong><em>The Black Dahlia</em></strong> (2006), a mystery thriller <strong><em>The Prestige</em></strong> alongside Hugh Jackman and <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/christian-charles-philip-bales-biography/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Christian Bale</a>, a rom-com <strong><em>The Nanny Diaries </em></strong>(2007) with <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/chris-evans-career-upcoming-projects-personal-life-achievements-net-worth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chris Evans</a>, <strong><em>Vicky Christina Barcelona</em></strong> (2008) and a superhero film <strong><em>The Spirit</em></strong> (2008). In all the movies, Johansson‚Äôs impact on the movies were strong and commendable.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1606" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Scarlett-Jo-300x188.jpg" alt="" width="579" height="363" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Suffice it to say, the association of Scarlett with <strong><em>The Marvels Cinematic Universe</em></strong> has proved to be fruitful for both the parties. She starred as Natasha Romanoff/ Black Widow in many Marvels movies starting with <strong><em>Iron Man 2</em></strong> in 2010. She then reprised the role in Marvel‚Äôs <strong><em>The Avengers</em></strong> (2012), <strong><em>Captain America: The Winter Soldier</em></strong> (2014), <strong><em>Avengers: Age of Ultron</em></strong> (2015), <strong><em>Captain America: Civil War</em></strong> (2016) alongside <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/chris-evans-career-upcoming-projects-personal-life-achievements-net-worth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chris Evans</a>, <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/chris-evans-career-upcoming-projects-personal-life-achievements-net-worth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chadwick Boseman</a>, <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/tom-holland-career-personal-life-net-worth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tom Holland</a> and many more and <strong><em>Thor Ragnorok</em></strong> (2017). Each of the movies are one of the highest grossing movies of all time and have smashed many box-office records both nationally and internationally. Scarlett had to work hard both physically and mentally in order to portray the role of Black Widow and she has done pure justice to that role.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Moreover, Johansson featured in a family drama <strong><em>We brought a Zoo</em></strong> (2011), a biographical drama <strong><em>Hitchcock</em></strong> (2012), a sci-fi film <strong><em>Under the Skin</em></strong> (2013), a solo sci-fi thriller movie <strong><em>Lucy</em></strong> (2014), a voice role in <strong><em>The Jingle Book </em></strong>(2016), a musical animated film <strong><em>Sing</em></strong> (2016) and a sci-fi action thriller ghost in <strong><em>The Shell</em></strong> (2017). Scarlett was immensely praised for her acting skills and her popularity grew more by the help of these projects.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>As a singer</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1607" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Scarlett-Johansson-Wallpaper-singing-300x223.jpg" alt="" width="585" height="434" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Scarlett is a multi-talented person. She sang for the first time in 2006 from the track <strong><em>‚ÄúSummertime‚Äù</em></strong> for <strong><em>Unexpected Dreams-Songs</em></strong> from <strong><em>The Stars</em></strong>. Later, in 2007 she appeared as a leading lady in Justin Timberlake song ‚Äú<strong><em>What Goes Around..Comes Around</em></strong>‚Äù. Johansson released her first debut album <strong><em>‚ÄúAnywhere I Lay My Head‚Äù</em></strong> in 2008 which was named as the 23<sup>rd</sup> best album of 2008 by NME. In the following year, she released a collaborative album named <strong><em>‚ÄúBreak Up‚Äù</em></strong> with Pete Yorn. In 2015, Johansson formed a band called <strong><em>The Singles</em></strong> and their first song was called <strong><em>‚ÄúCandy‚Äù</em></strong> later Los-Angeles based rock band Singles issued a cease and desist order demanding her to stop using their name. She has also performed in some songs for her movie <strong><em>The Jungle Book </em></strong>and<strong><em> Sing</em></strong> for which she got many positive reviews.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Upcoming Projects</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1608" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Scarlett-Johansson-Black-Widow-645x370-300x173.jpg" alt="" width="583" height="336" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Scarlett Johansson has been successful in giving box-office hits single-handedly. She is set to return as Natasha Romanoff/Black Widow in <strong><em>Avengers: Infinity War</em></strong> and its <strong><em>Untitled sequel</em></strong> in 2018 and 2019 respectively. She will also be seen in a <strong><em>Noah Baumbach Untitled project</em></strong> which will release in November, 2018. Scarlett will feature in a biographical drama <strong><em>The Beautiful</em></strong> and <strong><em>The Damned</em></strong> along with a voice role in <strong><em>Isle of Dogs</em></strong> which will release in 2018. Additionally, she has three movies to be released in 2019 namely a novel-based suspense drama <strong><em>Reflective Light</em></strong>, a psychological thriller <strong><em>Tangarine</em></strong> which is to be produced by George Clooney and a thriller drama <strong><em>The Psychopath Test</em></strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Personal Life</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1610" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/scarlett-johansson-divorce-daughter-rose-300x184.jpg" alt="" width="585" height="359" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Scarlett Johansson owns a lavish house in Manhattan and Los Angeles as well. She is Jewish and has an older sister Vanessa, an older brother Adrian, a twin brother Hunter and an older half-brother Christian. ‚ÄòScarJo‚Äô is the nickname given to Scarlett by her fans. She has had a very interesting love life. She dated many of her co-stars including Josh Hartnett. Scarlett was married for two years from 2008 to 2010 to actor Ryan Reynolds who is now married to<a href="http://wikiceleb.com/blake-lively-career-interest-personal-life-achievements-future-plans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Blake Lively</a>. Then she started dating the owner of an advertising agency Romain Dauriac in 2012. Scarlett and Romain married in 2014 and called it off officially in 2017. The couple has a daughter together named Rose Dorothy Dauriac born in 2014. Johansson also supports various charitable organizations such as Cancer Research UK, Stand Up to Cancer, Aid Still Required and so on.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Achievements</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1609" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wallpaper-2136276-300x182.jpg" alt="" width="582" height="353" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Scarlett is an amazing entertainer ergo she has been honored for many of her projects. She bagged <strong><em>Best Performance in a Feature Film: Leading Young Actress</em></strong> for her film <strong><em>An American Rhapsody</em></strong> in 2002. She won <strong><em>Best Actress in a Leading Role Award</em></strong> from <strong><em>British Academy Film Awards</em></strong> for her movie <strong><em>Lost in Translation</em></strong> in 2003 along with <strong><em>Palm Springs International Film Festival Rising Star Award </em></strong>for her movies <strong><em>Lost in Translation</em></strong> and <strong><em>Girl with a Pearl Earring</em></strong> in 2004. Johansson also won <strong><em>Toronto Films Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actress</em></strong> for <strong><em>Ghost World</em></strong> in 2001 and <strong><em>Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress</em></strong> for her role in <strong><em>Her</em></strong> in 2014. Furthermore, she acclaimed <strong><em>MTV movie award for Best Fight</em></strong> for <strong><em>Avengers </em></strong>in 2013.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>¬†</strong><strong>Net-Worth</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The stunning Scarlett Johansson is one of the top grossing actresses of Hollywood charging over $10 million per movie. She was the highest paid actress form 2014 to 2016. The net worth of Scarlett Johansson as of 2018 is reported to be $100 million.</p>
